_words: - Shampoo/conditioner/soap provided were smaller than what a hotel would provide for a place that sleeps 10 ( bring your own) - Ended up having to buy extra toilet paper/paper towels as we ran out with at most 7 people in the home at a time and no extras provided - Attempted to use grill several times and it did not heat up enough to be usable despite hooking up our own propane tank - Power was out overnight one night we were there (problematic for groceries/breastmilk) - There is a makeshift fire pit we never used, we would have loved an actual fire pit for cooking smores - Lack of AC was not an issue this time of year but would be in summer

_words: Its not our fist stay in this house, the place is nice however there are a few thing that could be looked after, minor details such a few electric plugs (damaged) kitchen extractor (very noisy) upstairs shower needs attention, the cleaning on the kitchen utensils (we had to wash everything before use, they were bad) lack of towels and bed linen, the garden furniture is poor as well, load of ants and other insects will appear as the windows and doors are probably 50y old and they let everything in, the only good side is the location of the propriety and the size that fit our needs, nevertheless the price is a bit on high side for all the conditions
